The paper discusses the use of surrogate models in genetic programming, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The focus is on optimizing the performance of the surrogate model, which is relevant to the field of neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY). The experiments involve symbolic regression, which is a common problem in software engineering (cs.SE).
